item.description:
When working with git you should have to use branches. But over the time, there will be a lot of branches that aren&rsquo;t needed anymore.
To get rid of this waste, I created a script to delete them:
#!/usr/bin/env bash BRANCHES=&#34;$(git branch --merged | grep -v &#34;\*&#34; | grep -v &#34;master&#34; | grep -v &#34;develop&#34;)&#34; if [ -z $BRANCHES ]; then echo &#34;No branch can deleted safely&#34; exit 1; fi echo &#34;The following branches will be deleted:&#34; echo $BRANCHES echo &#34;Are you sure?
